Moreover, local mining production failed to inspire confidence for economic recovery. However, the local unit gained after the trade-weighted dollar sunk against a basket of currencies. 

At the close of local trade, the rand quoted 0.77% stronger at R14.82/$, after trading in range of R14.82/$ - R14.97/$. The rand extended gains overnight. 

Expected range today R14.70/$ - R14.90/$.The JSE All Share (-0.18%) ended lower yesterday, in line with weak appetite for riskier assets. 

In local news, Mediclinic (-0.69%) – dual listed in Johannesburg and London – posted a 4% rise in half-year core earnings during the period ended 30 September 2019. 

The private hospital group’s earnings before interest, tax, depreciation and amortisation (EBITDA) climbed to £222m ($285.91 million)compared to last year’s £213m($274.32 million). In the overall emerging market sphere, the MSCI Emerging Market Index (-0.15% traded lower.
